
msgid "Packaging the application"
msgstr ""

msgid "$ tt pack TYPE [OPTION ...] .."
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"``tt pack`` packages an application into a distributable bundle of the "
"specified ``TYPE``:"
msgstr ""

msgid "``tgz``: create a ``.tgz`` archive."
msgstr ""

msgid "``deb``: create a DEB package."
msgstr ""

msgid "``rpm``: create an RPM package."
msgstr ""

msgid "The command below creates a DEB package for an application:"
msgstr ""

msgid "$ tt pack deb"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"This command generates a ``.deb`` file whose name depends on the environment"
" directory name and the operating system architecture, for example, ``test-"
"env_0.1.0.0-1_x86_64.deb``. You can also pass various :ref:`options <tt-"
"pack-options>` to the ``tt pack`` command to adjust generation properties, "
"for example, customize a bundle name, choose which artifacts should be "
"included, specify the required application dependencies."
msgstr ""

msgid "Options"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Include all artifacts in a bundle. In this case, a bundle might include "
"snapshots, WAL files, and logs."
msgstr ""

msgid "Specify the applications included in a bundle."
msgstr ""

msgid "**Example**"
msgstr ""

msgid "$ tt pack tgz --app-list app1,app3"
msgstr ""

msgid "**Applicable to:** ``tgz``"
msgstr ""

msgid "Package a Cartridge CLI-compatible archive."
msgstr ""

msgid "**Applicable to:** ``deb``, ``rpm``"
msgstr ""

msgid "Specify dependencies included in RPM and DEB packages."
msgstr ""

msgid "$ tt pack deb --deps 'wget,make>0.1.0,unzip>1,unzip<=7'"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Specify the path to a file containing dependencies included in RPM and DEB "
"packages. For example, the ``package-deps.txt`` file below contains several "
"dependencies and their versions:"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"unzip==6.0\n"
"neofetch>=6,<7\n"
"gcc>8"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"If this file is placed in the current directory, a ``tt pack`` command might"
" look like this:"
msgstr ""

msgid "$ tt pack deb --deps-file package-deps.txt"
msgstr ""

msgid "Specify a bundle name."
msgstr ""

msgid "$ tt pack tgz --filename sample-app.tar.gz"
msgstr ""

msgid "Specify a package name."
msgstr ""

msgid "$ tt pack tgz --name sample-app --version 1.0.1"
msgstr ""

msgid "Specify the path to a pre-install script for RPM and DEB packages."
msgstr ""

msgid "$ tt pack deb --preinst pre.sh"
msgstr ""

msgid "Specify the path to a post-install script for RPM and DEB packages."
msgstr ""

msgid "$ tt pack deb --postinst post.sh"
msgstr ""

msgid ""
"Build a package in an Ubuntu 18.04 Docker container. Before executing ``tt "
"pack`` with this option, make sure Docker is running."
msgstr ""

msgid "Specify a package version."
msgstr ""

msgid "Include Tarantool and ``tt`` binaries in a bundle."
msgstr ""

msgid "Don't include Tarantool and ``tt`` binaries in a bundle."
msgstr ""

msgid "Don't include external modules in a bundle."
msgstr ""
